This paper discusses the parallelization of stochastic simulations of biological systems on multi-core platforms, which involves designing efficient parallelization techniques. This topic falls under the category of computer science and specifically relates to modeling and simulation (cs.MS), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
